CNCP v1 23388
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#13746: the scoped style is not fully scoped",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:16:08.411896+00:00",
  "text": "the scoped style is not fully scoped\n\n### Vue version\n\n3.5.17\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nhttps://play.vuejs.org/#\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nthe scoped style is not fully scoped.\nit will affect outside components.\njust like https://github.com/vuejs/core/issues/6214\n\nif outside components use class root and hovered, .a will be red.\n\n<style scoped>\n.root:hover .a {\n  color: red;\n}\n</style>\n\n### What is expected?\n\n.root[xxx]:hover .a[xxx2] {\n  color: red;\n}\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\n.root:hover .a[xxx2] {\n  color: red;\n}\n\n### System Info\n\n```shell\n\n```\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\nIf this is unlikely to change as it would be a breaking change at this point, can a new method be added? like :scoped()?\nOr is there any way to better handle this type of case at present?",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "scope: compiler",
    ":hammer: p3-minor-bug"
  ],
